WEBVTT

00:18.600 --> 00:23.460
CHAPTER VII My first quarter at Lowood seemed an age,

00:23.780 --> 00:25.500
and not the Golden Age, either.

00:25.840 --> 00:28.820
It comprised an irksome struggle with difficulties

00:28.820 --> 00:31.940
in habituating myself to new rules and unwanted tasks.

00:32.960 --> 00:34.780
The fear of failure in these points

00:34.780 --> 00:37.780
harassed me worse than the physical hardships of my lot,

00:38.340 --> 00:39.800
though these were no trifles.

00:41.220 --> 00:45.900
During January, February, and part of March, the deep snows,

00:46.300 --> 00:49.160
and after the melting, the almost impassable roads

00:49.160 --> 00:51.900
prevented our stirring beyond the garden walls,

00:52.480 --> 00:53.740
except to go to church.

00:54.540 --> 00:57.840
But within these limits, we had to pass an hour every day

00:57.840 --> 00:58.900
in the open air.

00:59.480 --> 01:01.960
Our clothing was insufficient to protect us

01:01.960 --> 01:02.900
from the severe cold.

01:03.620 --> 01:04.680
We had no boots.

01:05.320 --> 01:07.780
The snow got into our shoes and melted there.

01:08.740 --> 01:12.020
Our ungloved hands became numbed and covered with chilglains,

01:12.880 --> 01:14.080
as were our feet.

01:15.160 --> 01:17.580
I remember well the distracting irritation

01:17.580 --> 01:19.720
I endured from this cause every evening,

01:20.240 --> 01:23.020
when my feet inflamed and the torture of thrusting

01:23.020 --> 01:26.800
the swelled, raw, and stiff toes into my shoes in the morning.

01:27.820 --> 01:30.600
Then the scanty supply of food was distressing.

01:31.500 --> 01:33.660
With a keen appetite of growing children,

01:34.140 --> 01:37.340
we had scarcely sufficient to keep alive a delicate invalid.

01:38.340 --> 01:40.160
From this deficiency of nourishment

01:40.160 --> 01:43.840
resulted in abuse, which pressed hardly on the younger pupils.

01:44.660 --> 01:47.480
Whenever the famished great girls had an opportunity,

01:47.880 --> 01:49.840
they would coax or menace the little ones out

01:49.840 --> 01:50.460
of their portion.

01:51.500 --> 01:54.820
Many a time I have shared between two claimants

01:54.820 --> 01:58.360
the precious morsel of brown bread distributed at teatime.

01:58.640 --> 02:02.140
And after relinquishing to a third half the contents

02:02.140 --> 02:04.860
of a mug of coffee, I have swallowed the remainder

02:04.860 --> 02:07.920
with an accompaniment of secret tears, forced for me

02:07.920 --> 02:09.580
by the exigency of hunger.

02:11.000 --> 02:13.300
Sundays were dreary days in that wintry season.

02:13.960 --> 02:16.760
We had to walk two miles to Brocklebridge Church,

02:17.320 --> 02:18.620
where our patron officiated.

02:19.420 --> 02:20.540
We set out cold.

02:20.880 --> 02:22.080
We arrived at Church colder.

02:22.960 --> 02:25.480
During the morning service, we became almost paralyzed.

02:26.260 --> 02:28.100
It was too far to return to dinner.

02:28.840 --> 02:30.720
And an allowance of cold meat and bread,

02:31.040 --> 02:33.480
in the same penorious proportion observed

02:33.480 --> 02:35.920
in our ordinary meals, was served round

02:35.920 --> 02:36.820
between the services.

02:38.320 --> 02:40.060
At the close of the afternoon service,

02:40.500 --> 02:42.760
we returned by an exposed and hilly road,

02:43.740 --> 02:45.700
where the bitter winter wind, blowing

02:45.700 --> 02:47.860
over a range of snowy summits to the north,

02:47.860 --> 02:50.300
almost flayed the skin from our faces.

02:51.520 --> 02:53.180
I can remember Miss Temple walking

02:53.180 --> 02:56.240
lightly and rapidly along our drooping line,

02:56.580 --> 02:59.940
her plaid cloak, which the frosty wind fluttered,

03:00.180 --> 03:03.160
gathered close about her, and encouraging us,

03:03.360 --> 03:06.380
by precept and example, to keep up our spirits

03:06.740 --> 03:10.580
and march forward, as she said, like stalwart soldiers.

03:11.600 --> 03:15.260
The other teachers, poor things, were generally themselves

03:15.260 --> 03:19.100
too much dejected to attempt the task of cheering others.

03:21.080 --> 03:23.860
How we longed for the light and heat of a blazing fire

03:23.860 --> 03:25.220
when we got back.

03:25.720 --> 03:28.460
But to the little ones, at least, this was denied.

03:29.080 --> 03:31.960
Each hearth in the schoolroom was immediately surrounded

03:31.960 --> 03:35.140
by a double row of great girls, and behind them,

03:35.400 --> 03:37.000
the younger children crouched in groups,

03:37.400 --> 03:39.900
wrapping their starved arms in their pinafores.

03:40.560 --> 03:42.260
A little solace came at tea time,

03:42.740 --> 03:44.720
in the shape of a double ration of bread,

03:44.720 --> 03:47.180
a whole instead of a half slice,

03:47.900 --> 03:50.720
with a delicious addition of a thin scrape of butter.

03:51.380 --> 03:54.020
It was the hebdominal treat to which we all looked forward

03:54.020 --> 03:55.280
from Sabbath to Sabbath.

03:56.100 --> 03:58.480
I generally contrived to reserve a moiety

03:58.480 --> 04:00.580
of this boundary past for myself,

04:01.420 --> 04:04.300
but the remainder I was invariably obliged to part with.

04:05.380 --> 04:08.320
The Sunday evening was spent in repeating, by heart,

04:08.720 --> 04:11.580
the church catechism and the fifth, sixth,

04:11.600 --> 04:13.340
and seventh chapters of St. Matthew,

04:13.860 --> 04:16.980
and in listening to a long sermon read by Miss Miller,

04:17.360 --> 04:19.720
whose irrepressible yawns attested her weariness.

04:20.720 --> 04:22.480
A frequent interlude of these performances

04:22.480 --> 04:24.940
was the enactment of the part of Eudicus

04:24.940 --> 04:27.100
by some half dozen of little girls,

04:27.660 --> 04:30.400
who, overpowered with sleep, would fall down,

04:30.820 --> 04:33.980
if not out of the third loft, yet off the fourth form,

04:34.760 --> 04:36.260
and be taken up half dead.

04:36.760 --> 04:39.140
The remedy was to thrust them forward

04:39.140 --> 04:40.660
into the center of the schoolroom

04:40.660 --> 04:43.640
and oblige them to stand there till the sermon was finished.

04:44.380 --> 04:46.100
Sometimes their feet failed them,

04:46.480 --> 04:48.040
and they sank together in a heap.

04:48.740 --> 04:51.820
They were then propped up with the monitor's high stools.

04:53.060 --> 04:56.140
I have not yet alluded to the visits of Mr. Brocklehurst,

04:56.580 --> 04:58.520
and indeed that gentleman was from home

04:58.520 --> 05:00.220
during the greater part of the first month

05:00.220 --> 05:01.160
after my arrival.

05:01.900 --> 05:04.660
Perhaps prolonging his stay with his friend, the archdeacon,

05:05.180 --> 05:06.860
his absence was a relief to me.

05:07.340 --> 05:09.420
I need not say that I have my own reasons

05:09.420 --> 05:12.400
for dreading his coming, but come he did at last.

05:13.120 --> 05:16.640
One afternoon, I had then been three weeks at Lowood,

05:17.080 --> 05:19.580
as I was sitting with a slate in my hand,

05:19.840 --> 05:21.700
puzzling over a sum and long division,

05:22.200 --> 05:24.960
my eyes, raised in abstraction to the window,

05:25.500 --> 05:27.480
caught sight of a figure just passing.

05:28.440 --> 05:31.960
I recognized almost instinctively that gaunt outline,

05:32.420 --> 05:35.220
and when, two minutes after, all the school,

05:35.540 --> 05:37.880
teachers included, rose en masse,

05:37.880 --> 05:40.060
it was not necessary for me to look up

05:40.060 --> 05:43.120
in order to ascertain whose entrance they thus greeted.

05:44.220 --> 05:46.260
A long stride measured the schoolroom,

05:46.680 --> 05:49.800
and presently beside Miss Temple, who herself had risen,

05:50.500 --> 05:53.200
stood the same black column which had frowned on me

05:53.200 --> 05:55.840
so ominously from the hearth rug of Gateshead.

05:56.920 --> 05:59.980
I now glance sideways at this piece of architecture.

06:00.340 --> 06:03.780
Yes, I was right, it was Mr. Brocklehurst,

06:04.300 --> 06:07.020
buttoned up in a certut, and looking longer,

06:07.500 --> 06:09.540
narrower, and more rigid than ever.

06:11.240 --> 06:14.560
I had my own reasons for being dismayed at this apparition.

06:15.180 --> 06:17.640
Too well I remembered the perfidious hints

06:17.640 --> 06:21.360
given by Mrs. Reed about my disposition, et cetera,

06:21.940 --> 06:24.120
the promise pledged by Mr. Brocklehurst

06:24.120 --> 06:27.600
to reprise Miss Temple and the teachers of a vicious nature.

06:28.440 --> 06:30.260
All along, I had been dreading

06:30.260 --> 06:31.660
the fulfillment of this promise.

06:32.000 --> 06:34.680
I had been looking out daily for the coming man,

06:35.040 --> 06:38.520
whose information respecting my past life and conversation

06:38.520 --> 06:40.820
was to brand me as a bad child forever.

06:41.360 --> 06:42.960
Now, there he was.

06:43.620 --> 06:45.860
He stood at Miss Temple's side.

06:46.220 --> 06:48.020
He was speaking low in her ear.

06:48.480 --> 06:51.920
I did not doubt he was making disclosures of my villainy,

06:52.100 --> 06:54.720
and I watched her eye with painful anxiety,

06:55.180 --> 06:58.780
expecting every moment to see its dark orb turn on me

06:58.780 --> 07:00.860
a glance of repugnance and contempt.

07:01.660 --> 07:04.620
I listened, too, and as I happened to be seated

07:04.620 --> 07:07.860
quite at the top of the room, I caught most of what he said.

07:08.260 --> 07:11.000
Its import relieved me from immediate apprehension.

07:11.920 --> 07:14.800
I suppose, Miss Temple, the thread I bought at Loughton

07:14.800 --> 07:15.360
will do.

07:15.700 --> 07:18.100
It struck me that it would be just of the quality

07:18.100 --> 07:21.460
for the calico chemises, and I sorted the needles to match.

07:21.980 --> 07:24.400
You may tell Miss Smith that I forgot to make

07:24.400 --> 07:26.120
a memorandum of the darning needles,

07:26.560 --> 07:29.120
but she shall have some papers sent in next week,

07:29.120 --> 07:32.080
and she is not on any account to give out more

07:32.080 --> 07:33.680
than one at a time to each pupil.

07:34.280 --> 07:36.580
If they have more, they are apt to be careless

07:36.580 --> 07:39.200
and lose them, and oh, ma'am.

07:39.380 --> 07:41.800
I wish the woolen stockings were better looked to.

07:42.280 --> 07:45.000
When I was here last, I went into the kitchen garden

07:45.000 --> 07:47.500
and examined the clothes drying on the line.

07:47.820 --> 07:49.540
There was a quantity of black hose

07:49.540 --> 07:51.440
in a very bad state of repair.

07:52.160 --> 07:53.620
From the size of the holes in them,

07:53.620 --> 07:56.680
I was sure they had not been well mended from time to time.

07:57.260 --> 07:58.000
He paused.

07:59.120 --> 08:02.340
Your direction shall be attended to, sir, said Miss Temple.

08:03.200 --> 08:05.840
And ma'am, he continued, the laundress tells me

08:05.840 --> 08:08.280
some of the girls have two clean tuckers in the week.

08:08.740 --> 08:09.560
It is too much.

08:09.960 --> 08:11.440
The rules limit them to one.

08:12.820 --> 08:14.980
I think I can explain that circumstance, sir.

08:15.580 --> 08:17.980
Agnes and Catherine Johnstone were invited to take tea

08:17.980 --> 08:19.820
with some friends at Loughton last Thursday,

08:20.180 --> 08:22.320
and I gave them leave to put on clean tuckers

08:22.320 --> 08:23.000
for the occasion.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.360
Mr. Brocklehurst nodded.

08:26.260 --> 08:28.140
Well, for once it may pass,

08:28.140 --> 08:31.240
but please not to let the circumstance occur too often.

08:31.820 --> 08:33.920
And there is another thing which surprised me.

08:34.120 --> 08:36.860
I find in settling accounts with the housekeeper

08:36.860 --> 08:39.700
that a lunch consisting of bread and cheese

08:39.700 --> 08:41.780
has twice been served out to the girls

08:41.780 --> 08:42.920
during the past fortnight.

08:43.620 --> 08:44.420
How is this?

08:44.860 --> 08:46.200
I looked over the regulations

08:46.200 --> 08:48.420
and I find no such meal as lunch mentioned.

08:49.100 --> 08:50.520
Who introduced this innovation?

08:50.900 --> 08:51.920
And by what authority?

08:53.260 --> 08:55.940
I must be responsible for the circumstance, sir,

08:56.420 --> 08:57.240
replied Miss Temple.

08:57.680 --> 08:59.460
The breakfast was so ill-prepared

08:59.460 --> 09:02.140
that the pupils could not possibly eat it,

09:02.220 --> 09:04.200
and I dared not allow them to remain fasting

09:04.200 --> 09:05.100
till dinner time.

09:06.220 --> 09:07.940
Madam, allow me an instant.

09:08.360 --> 09:10.760
You are aware that my plan in bringing up these girls

09:10.760 --> 09:14.260
is not to accustom them to habits of luxury and indulgence,

09:14.520 --> 09:17.700
but to render them hearty, patient, self-denying.

09:18.120 --> 09:20.360
Should any little accidental disappointment

09:20.360 --> 09:23.700
of the appetite occur, such as the spoiling of a meal,

09:24.080 --> 09:26.120
the under or the overdressing of a dish,

09:26.120 --> 09:28.860
the incident ought not to be neutralized

09:28.860 --> 09:30.740
by replacing with something more delicate

09:30.740 --> 09:32.020
the comfort lost,

09:32.400 --> 09:33.820
thus pampering the body

09:33.820 --> 09:36.120
and obviating the sum of this institution.

09:36.840 --> 09:38.020
It ought to be improved

09:38.020 --> 09:40.320
to the spiritual edification of the pupils

09:40.740 --> 09:42.700
by encouraging them to evince fortitude

09:42.700 --> 09:43.900
under temporary probation.

09:44.760 --> 09:48.180
A brief address on those occasions would not be mistimed,

09:48.320 --> 09:49.800
wherein a judicious instructor

09:49.800 --> 09:52.960
would take the opportunity of referring to the sufferings

09:52.960 --> 09:54.180
of the primitive Christians

09:54.180 --> 09:56.240
to the torments of martyrs,

09:56.440 --> 09:58.840
to the exhortations of our blessed Lord himself,

09:59.320 --> 10:00.640
calling upon his disciples

10:00.640 --> 10:02.460
to take up the cross and follow him,

10:02.880 --> 10:05.280
to his warnings that man should not live by bread alone,

10:05.460 --> 10:08.080
but by every word that proceedeth out of the mouth of God,

10:08.540 --> 10:10.280
to his divine consolations.

10:10.780 --> 10:13.880
If ye suffer hunger or thirst for my sake, happy are ye.

10:14.380 --> 10:16.680
Oh, madam, when you put bread and cheese

10:16.680 --> 10:19.140
instead of burnt porridge into these children's mouths,

10:19.480 --> 10:21.580
you may indeed feed their vile bodies,

10:21.580 --> 10:24.480
but you little think how you starve their immortal souls.

10:25.640 --> 10:27.380
Mr. Brocklehurst again paused,

10:27.960 --> 10:29.720
perhaps overcome by his feelings.

10:30.540 --> 10:31.700
Miss Temple had looked down

10:31.700 --> 10:33.320
when he first began to speak to her,

10:33.640 --> 10:35.640
but she now gazed straight before her,

10:35.780 --> 10:38.120
and her face, naturally pale as marble,

10:38.760 --> 10:41.260
appeared to be assuming also the coldness

10:41.260 --> 10:44.580
and fixity of that material, especially her mouth,

10:45.060 --> 10:46.480
closed as if it would have required

10:46.480 --> 10:48.600
a sculptor's chisel to open it,

10:48.660 --> 10:50.560
and her brow settled gradually

10:50.560 --> 10:52.100
into petrified severity.

10:53.720 --> 10:56.780
Meantime, Mr. Brocklehurst, standing on the hearth

10:56.780 --> 10:58.700
with his hands behind his back,

10:58.900 --> 11:00.720
majestically surveyed the whole school.

11:01.220 --> 11:03.320
Suddenly, his eyes gave a blink,

11:03.720 --> 11:04.880
as if it had meant something

11:04.880 --> 11:07.060
that either dazzled or shocked its pupil.

11:07.960 --> 11:10.240
Turning, he said in more rapid accents

11:10.240 --> 11:11.620
that he had hitherto used,

11:12.120 --> 11:14.180
Miss Temple, Miss Temple, what?

11:14.520 --> 11:16.320
What is that girl with curled hair?

11:16.780 --> 11:19.620
Red hair, ma'am, curled, curled all over.

11:20.560 --> 11:23.880
And extending his cane, he pointed to the awful object,

11:24.400 --> 11:26.260
his hand shaking as he did so.

11:26.960 --> 11:30.100
It is Julia Severn, replied Miss Temple very quietly.

11:31.080 --> 11:33.440
Julia Severn, ma'am, and why has she

11:33.440 --> 11:35.080
or any other curled hair?

11:35.740 --> 11:37.600
Why, in defiance of every precept

11:37.600 --> 11:39.040
and principle of this house,

11:39.360 --> 11:41.160
does she conform to the world so openly,

11:41.820 --> 11:44.840
here in an evangelical charitable establishment

11:44.840 --> 11:47.140
as to where her hair one mass of curls?

11:48.580 --> 11:50.300
Julia's hair curls naturally,

11:50.420 --> 11:52.500
returned Miss Temple, still more quietly.

11:53.440 --> 11:56.280
Naturally, yes, but we are not to conform to nature.

11:56.900 --> 11:59.120
I wish these girls to be the children of grace,

11:59.180 --> 12:00.540
and why that abundance?

12:01.200 --> 12:03.160
I have again and again intimated

12:03.160 --> 12:05.560
that I desire the hair to be arranged closely,

12:05.900 --> 12:07.360
modestly, plainly.

12:07.360 --> 12:10.240
Miss Temple, that girl's hair must be cut off entirely.

12:10.700 --> 12:12.320
I will send a borrower tomorrow,

12:12.320 --> 12:15.520
and I see others who are far too much of the excretions.

12:16.060 --> 12:18.160
That tall girl, tell her to turn round.

12:18.940 --> 12:20.540
Tell all the first form to rise up

12:20.540 --> 12:21.960
and direct their faces to the wall.

12:22.760 --> 12:24.980
Miss Temple passed her handkerchief over her lips,

12:25.340 --> 12:27.560
as if to smooth away the involuntary smile

12:27.560 --> 12:28.380
that curled them.

12:28.800 --> 12:30.060
She gave the order, however,

12:30.300 --> 12:31.840
and when the first class could take in

12:31.840 --> 12:34.200
what was required of them, they obeyed.

12:34.740 --> 12:36.300
Leaning a little back on my bench,

12:36.720 --> 12:38.200
I could see the looks and grimaces

12:38.200 --> 12:40.140
with which they commented on this maneuver.

12:40.600 --> 12:43.620
It was a pity Mr. Rocklehurst could not see them, too.

12:43.620 --> 12:45.460
He would perhaps have felt that.

12:45.820 --> 12:48.320
Whatever he might do with the outside of the cup and platter,

12:48.760 --> 12:50.800
the inside was farther beyond his interference

12:50.800 --> 12:51.640
than he imagined.

12:52.860 --> 12:55.140
He scrutinized the reverse of these living medals

12:55.140 --> 12:57.860
some five minutes, then pronounced sentence.

12:58.580 --> 13:00.780
These words fell like the knell of doom.

13:01.640 --> 13:03.840
All those top knots must be cut off.

13:04.840 --> 13:06.660
Miss Temple seemed to remonstrate.

13:07.560 --> 13:08.340
Madam, he would.

13:08.880 --> 13:10.380
I have a master to serve,

13:10.740 --> 13:12.260
whose kingdom is not of this world.

13:12.960 --> 13:15.580
My mission is to mortify in these girls

13:15.580 --> 13:16.920
the lust of the flesh,

13:17.280 --> 13:18.880
to teach them to clothe themselves

13:18.880 --> 13:20.860
with shame-facedness and sobriety,

13:21.220 --> 13:23.540
not with braided hair and costly apparel.

13:23.840 --> 13:25.520
And each of the young persons before us

13:25.520 --> 13:27.620
has a string of hair twisted in plates,

13:28.000 --> 13:29.640
which vanity itself might have woven.

13:30.000 --> 13:31.820
These, I repeat, must be cut off.

13:32.120 --> 13:35.000
Think of the time wasted of...

13:35.000 --> 13:37.000
Mr. Rocklehurst was here interrupted.

13:37.620 --> 13:41.160
Three other visitors, ladies, now entered the room.

13:41.700 --> 13:43.620
They ought to have come a little sooner

13:43.620 --> 13:45.660
to have heard his lecture on dress,

13:46.020 --> 13:47.780
for they were splendidly attired

13:47.780 --> 13:49.800
in velvet, silk, and furs.

13:50.580 --> 13:52.000
The two younger of the trio,

13:52.540 --> 13:54.440
fine girls of 16 and 17,

13:54.660 --> 13:57.540
had gray beaver hats, then in fashion,

13:58.360 --> 13:59.920
shaded with ostrich plumes,

14:00.380 --> 14:03.160
and from under the brim of this graceful headdress

14:03.160 --> 14:06.480
fell a profusion of light tresses elaborately curled.

14:07.140 --> 14:10.320
The elder lady was enveloped in a costly velvet shawl,

14:10.320 --> 14:12.180
trimmed with ermine,

14:12.840 --> 14:15.160
and she wore a false front of French girls.

14:16.600 --> 14:19.780
These ladies were deferentially received by Miss Temple

14:19.780 --> 14:22.680
as Mrs. and Mrs. Rocklehurst,

14:23.720 --> 14:26.300
and conducted to seats of honor at the top of the room.

14:26.920 --> 14:28.740
It seems they had come in the carriage

14:28.740 --> 14:30.220
with their reverend relative,

14:30.720 --> 14:32.820
and had been conducting a rummaging scrutiny

14:32.820 --> 14:34.080
of the room upstairs,

14:34.720 --> 14:37.140
while he transacted business with the housekeeper,

14:37.860 --> 14:38.800
questioned the laundress,

14:38.800 --> 14:40.500
and lectured the superintendent.

14:41.560 --> 14:44.100
They now proceeded to address diverse remarks

14:44.100 --> 14:45.560
and reproofs to Miss Smith,

14:46.040 --> 14:47.660
who was charged with the care of the linen

14:47.660 --> 14:49.580
in the inspection of the dormitories,

14:50.140 --> 14:52.340
but I had no time to listen to what they said.

14:53.440 --> 14:55.900
Other matters called off and enchanted my attention.

14:57.100 --> 14:59.280
Hitherto, while gathering up the discourse

14:59.280 --> 15:01.120
of Mrs. Rocklehurst and Miss Temple,

15:01.640 --> 15:03.320
I had not, at the same time,

15:03.700 --> 15:06.120
neglected precautions to secure my personal safety,

15:06.500 --> 15:08.220
which I thought would be effected

15:08.220 --> 15:09.920
if I could only elude observation.

15:10.620 --> 15:13.500
To this end, I had sat well back on the form,

15:14.140 --> 15:15.960
and while seeming to be busy with my sum,

15:16.260 --> 15:19.700
had held my slate in such a manner as to conceal my face.

15:20.240 --> 15:21.740
I might have escaped noticed,

15:22.580 --> 15:23.860
had not my treacherous slate

15:23.860 --> 15:26.260
somehow happened to slip from my hand

15:26.260 --> 15:28.860
and fallen with an obtrusive crash,

15:29.160 --> 15:31.160
directly drawn every eye upon me.

15:31.500 --> 15:33.200
I knew it was all over now,

15:33.560 --> 15:36.200
and as I stooped up to pick up the two fragments of slate,

15:36.200 --> 15:38.120
I rallied my forces for the worst.

15:38.660 --> 15:39.360
It came.

15:40.460 --> 15:43.400
A careless girl, said Mr. Rocklehurst,

15:43.920 --> 15:47.400
and immediately after, it is the new pupil I perceive.

15:48.100 --> 15:49.520
And before I could draw a breath,

15:49.840 --> 15:52.400
I must not forget I have a word to say respecting her.

15:53.140 --> 15:55.580
That aloud, how loud it seemed to me,

15:55.860 --> 15:57.700
let the child who broke her slate come forward.

15:59.120 --> 16:00.920
Of my own accord, I could not have stirred.

16:01.620 --> 16:04.540
I was paralyzed, but the two great girls

16:04.540 --> 16:06.640
who sat on each side of me,

16:07.220 --> 16:09.860
set me on my legs and pushed me towards the dread judge.

16:10.580 --> 16:13.980
And then Miss Temple gently assisted me to his very feet,

16:14.400 --> 16:15.820
and I caught her whispered counsel.

16:16.620 --> 16:17.780
Don't be afraid, Jane.

16:18.200 --> 16:19.420
I saw it was an accident.

16:20.280 --> 16:21.440
You shall not be punished.

16:22.480 --> 16:24.640
The kind whisper went to my heart like a dagger.

16:26.240 --> 16:28.800
Another minute, and she'll despise me for hypocrite,

16:28.840 --> 16:31.760
thought I, and an impulse of fury

16:31.760 --> 16:34.540
against Reed, Rocklehurst, and company

16:34.540 --> 16:37.200
bounded in my pulses at the conviction.

16:37.700 --> 16:39.040
I was no Helen Burns.

16:40.520 --> 16:42.940
Fetch that stool, said Mr. Rocklehurst,

16:43.500 --> 16:44.900
pointing to a very high one

16:44.900 --> 16:46.880
from which a monitor had just risen.

16:47.180 --> 16:47.980
It was brought.

16:48.740 --> 16:50.220
Place the child upon it.

16:51.160 --> 16:53.960
And I was placed there, by whom I don't know.

16:54.600 --> 16:56.740
I was in no condition to note particulars.

16:57.160 --> 16:59.660
I was only aware that they had hoisted me up

16:59.660 --> 17:01.940
to the height of Mr. Rocklehurst's nose,

17:02.860 --> 17:04.520
that he was within a yard of me,

17:04.580 --> 17:07.720
and that a spread of shot orange and purple silk polices

17:07.720 --> 17:11.640
and a cloud of silvery plumage extended and waved below me.

17:12.580 --> 17:13.940
Mr. Rocklehurst hemmed.

17:14.160 --> 17:16.840
Ladies, said he, turning to his family,

17:17.340 --> 17:19.240
Miss Temple, teachers, and children,

17:19.440 --> 17:20.600
you all see this girl?

17:21.200 --> 17:24.180
Of course they did, for I felt their eyes directed

17:24.180 --> 17:26.640
like burning glasses against my scorched skin.

17:27.500 --> 17:29.440
You see she is yet young.

17:30.080 --> 17:31.700
You observe that she possesses

17:31.700 --> 17:33.120
the ordinary form of childhood.

17:33.860 --> 17:35.720
God has graciously given her the shape

17:35.720 --> 17:37.200
that he has given to all of us.

17:37.540 --> 17:40.520
No signal deformity points her out as a marked character.

17:41.060 --> 17:42.860
Who would think that the evil one

17:42.860 --> 17:45.480
has already found a servant and agent in her?

17:45.820 --> 17:48.320
Yet such, I grieve to say, is the case.

17:49.640 --> 17:54.000
A pause, in which I began to steady the palsy of my nerves,

17:54.400 --> 17:56.320
and to feel that the Rubicon had passed.

17:56.820 --> 17:59.840
And that the trial, no longer to be shirked,

18:00.080 --> 18:01.280
must be firmly sustained.

18:02.740 --> 18:06.440
My dear children, pursued the black marble clergyman,

18:06.660 --> 18:10.300
with pathos, this is a sad, a melancholy occasion.

18:10.940 --> 18:13.660
For it becomes my duty to warn you that this girl,

18:13.780 --> 18:17.240
who might be one of God's own lambs, is a little cast away.

18:17.760 --> 18:19.380
Not a member of the true flock,

18:19.780 --> 18:22.140
but evidently an interloper and an alien.

18:22.620 --> 18:24.480
You must be on your guard against her.

18:24.480 --> 18:26.020
You must shun her example.

18:26.400 --> 18:28.460
If necessary, avoid her company.

18:29.060 --> 18:30.260
Exclude her from your sports,

18:30.700 --> 18:32.240
and shut her out from your converse.

18:32.920 --> 18:34.520
Teachers, you must watch her.

18:34.720 --> 18:36.060
Keep your eyes on her movements.

18:36.540 --> 18:37.500
Weigh well her words.

18:37.900 --> 18:38.980
Scrutinize her actions.

18:39.260 --> 18:40.880
Punish her body to save her soul.

18:41.640 --> 18:44.180
If, indeed, such salvation be possible.

18:44.760 --> 18:47.840
For, my tongue falters while I tell it,

18:48.120 --> 18:51.600
this girl, this child, the native of a Christian land,

18:52.080 --> 18:53.480
worse than many a little heathen

18:53.480 --> 18:56.520
who says its prayers to Brahma and kneels before Juggernaut,

18:56.920 --> 18:58.860
this girl is a liar.

19:00.540 --> 19:02.700
Now came a pause of 10 minutes,

19:03.100 --> 19:05.180
during which I, by this time,

19:05.540 --> 19:07.380
in perfect possession of my wits,

19:07.920 --> 19:10.040
observed all the female Brocklehursts

19:10.040 --> 19:11.840
produce their pocket handkerchiefs

19:11.840 --> 19:13.180
and apply them to their optics,

19:13.900 --> 19:16.480
while the elderly lady swayed herself to and fro,

19:16.880 --> 19:18.940
and the two younger ones whispered, how shocking.

19:19.840 --> 19:21.180
Mr. Brocklehurst resumed.

19:21.820 --> 19:24.120
This I learned from her benefactress,

19:24.740 --> 19:26.400
from the pious and charitable lady

19:26.400 --> 19:28.440
who adopted her in her orphaned state,

19:28.900 --> 19:30.320
reared her as her own daughter,

19:30.680 --> 19:32.460
and whose kindness, whose generosity,

19:32.780 --> 19:36.040
the unhappy girl repaid by an ingratitude so bad,

19:36.260 --> 19:39.100
so dreadful, that at last her excellent patroness

19:39.100 --> 19:42.060
was obliged to separate her from her own young ones,

19:42.620 --> 19:44.660
fearful lest her vicious examples

19:44.660 --> 19:46.080
should contaminate their purity.

19:46.740 --> 19:48.760
She has sent her here to be healed.

19:49.460 --> 19:51.700
Even as the Jews of old sent their disease

19:51.700 --> 19:53.440
to the troubled pool of Bethesda,

19:54.020 --> 19:55.720
and teachers, superintendent,

19:56.240 --> 19:58.380
I beg of you not to allow the waters

19:58.380 --> 19:59.720
to stagnate around her.

20:00.620 --> 20:02.180
With this sublime conclusion,

20:02.660 --> 20:05.680
Mr. Brocklehurst adjusted the top button of her Sertut,

20:06.280 --> 20:08.360
muttered something to his family, who rose,

20:08.740 --> 20:09.820
bowed to Miss Temple,

20:10.100 --> 20:13.460
and then all the great people sailed in state from the room.

20:14.520 --> 20:16.540
Turning at the door, my judge said,

20:17.340 --> 20:19.960
Let her stand half an hour longer on that stool,

20:20.300 --> 20:22.860
and let no one speak to her during the remainder of the day.

20:24.380 --> 20:27.060
There was I then, mounted aloft,

20:27.420 --> 20:30.060
I, who had said I could not bear the shame

20:30.060 --> 20:33.060
of standing on my natural feet in the middle of the room,

20:33.680 --> 20:36.860
was now exposed to general view on a pedestal of infamy.

20:37.740 --> 20:40.880
What my sensations were no language can describe,

20:41.560 --> 20:44.380
but just as they all rose, stifling my breath,

20:44.740 --> 20:45.860
and constricting my throat,

20:45.860 --> 20:47.880
a girl came up and passed me.

20:48.080 --> 20:50.220
In passing, she lifted her eyes.

20:50.820 --> 20:52.580
What a strange light inspired them!

20:53.060 --> 20:55.960
What an extraordinary sensation that rays sent through me!

20:56.500 --> 20:58.100
How the new feeling bore me up!

20:58.560 --> 21:02.400
It was as if a martyr, a hero, had passed a slave or victim,

21:02.920 --> 21:04.720
and imparted strength in the transit.

21:05.420 --> 21:08.540
I mastered the rising hysteria, lifted up my head,

21:08.920 --> 21:10.580
and took a firm stand on the stool.

21:11.260 --> 21:13.020
Helen Burns asked some slight question

21:13.020 --> 21:14.780
about her work of Miss Smith.

21:14.780 --> 21:17.700
Was chidden for the triviality of the inquiry,

21:18.460 --> 21:21.560
returned to her place, and smiled at me as she again went by.

21:22.040 --> 21:22.880
What a smile!

21:23.660 --> 21:26.440
I remember it now, and I know that it was the effluence

21:26.440 --> 21:28.520
of fine intellect, of true courage.

21:29.100 --> 21:31.680
It lit up her marked liniments, her thin face,

21:31.960 --> 21:34.340
her sunken gray eye, like a reflection

21:34.340 --> 21:35.820
from the aspect of an angel.

21:36.500 --> 21:39.720
Yet at that moment Helen Burns wore on her arm

21:40.340 --> 21:41.520
the untidy badge.

21:42.380 --> 21:44.500
Scarcely an hour ago I had heard her condemned

21:44.500 --> 21:47.120
by Miss Scatchard to a dinner of bread and water

21:47.120 --> 21:49.960
on the morrow, because she had blotted in exercise

21:49.960 --> 21:50.980
and copying it out.

21:52.220 --> 21:54.080
Such is the imperfect nature of man.

21:54.780 --> 21:57.660
Such spots are there on the disk of the clearest planet,

21:58.320 --> 22:00.080
and eyes like Miss Scatchard's can only

22:00.080 --> 22:03.740
see those minute defects and are blind to the full brightness

22:03.740 --> 22:04.500
of the orb.

22:06.380 --> 22:07.600
End of chapter 7.

